WEBVTT

00:05.463 --> 00:07.590
-MELANIE: Get out.
-ARTIE: I just want to talk
for a minute, okay? That's all.

00:07.632 --> 00:09.592
-MELANIE: There's nothing
to talk about.
-ARTIE: What...

00:09.634 --> 00:11.469
-MELANIE: Go.
-ARTIE: It's a little setback,
all right?

00:11.553 --> 00:14.139
-I can make it all right.
-MELANIE: A little setback?

00:14.180 --> 00:16.641
Are-are you kidding me?
You've ruined our lives.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.518
-ARTIE: All right.
-MELANIE: You destroyed us.

00:18.601 --> 00:20.645
ARTIE: No, no, you're being
a little overdramatic right now.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.939
MELANIE:
Get the fuck out
before I kill you.

00:22.981 --> 00:24.232
ARTIE:
Baby, come on, come on.

00:24.315 --> 00:26.443
MELANIE:
Take your shit and leave!

00:26.484 --> 00:29.362
ARTIE:
All right! Okay. Jesus.

00:31.197 --> 00:32.907
-If I go...
-MELANIE: Go!

00:32.991 --> 00:35.118
(grunts)

00:36.161 --> 00:37.746
(glass shatters)

01:00.018 --> 01:02.604
(phone ringing)

01:03.688 --> 01:04.897
-Yeah?
-ARTIE: Hey, it's, uh,

01:04.980 --> 01:07.233
-536.
-536.

01:07.317 --> 01:09.527
I got you minus 12 grand.

01:09.569 --> 01:12.280
Fucking Saints, am I right?

01:12.364 --> 01:14.032
-Yes, you are.
-I mean, you're gonna

01:14.074 --> 01:17.535
cover the spread. Just pull
your panties out of your ass and

01:17.577 --> 01:20.372
-take a knee.
-Okay, what do you like?

01:20.413 --> 01:23.792
-A three-game parlay.
-Go.

01:23.875 --> 01:26.711
K.C. minus six and a half.

01:26.795 --> 01:29.130
Uh... Browns/Ravens,

01:29.214 --> 01:31.216
first quarter under ten.

01:32.258 --> 01:34.551
And the Jags plus
three and a half.

01:34.594 --> 01:36.846
Uh, hook's gonna cost you
a buck 30.

01:36.888 --> 01:38.223
Really?

01:38.306 --> 01:39.890
Yeah, line moved
about 20 minutes ago.

01:39.973 --> 01:41.893
Fuck.

01:43.561 --> 01:46.481
Okay. All right.
Get me down for a grand.

01:47.273 --> 01:48.775
All right, you lose,
you're over.

01:48.858 --> 01:50.652
I'm gonna need
to see you next week.

01:52.112 --> 01:54.072
Yeah. You don't like the play?

01:54.155 --> 01:55.740
Who cares what I like?

01:55.782 --> 01:58.368
It's just hard to get
three things right in the NFL.

02:00.036 --> 02:01.246
I like it.

02:01.329 --> 02:04.249
-You're down. Good luck.
-(phone ringing)

02:07.961 --> 02:09.963
(sighs)

02:10.045 --> 02:11.756
Hi, honey.

02:11.798 --> 02:13.717
-SANDRA (over phone):
We got a problem.
-Go.

02:13.758 --> 02:15.135
Go?

02:15.218 --> 02:17.303
I'm not one of your
scumbag losers.

02:17.387 --> 02:19.305
What do you need?

02:19.389 --> 02:22.017
-$1,500.
-I just gave you three grand.

02:22.100 --> 02:24.811
-My Invisalign, hello.
-Why you doing that?

02:24.894 --> 02:26.271
I like your snaggletooth.

02:26.353 --> 02:27.981
Also, Anthony's tuition's due.

02:28.064 --> 02:30.692
A-At what point is his father
gonna kick in a few bucks?

02:30.775 --> 02:32.192
-(phone ringing)
-His father's in a psych ward

02:32.277 --> 02:34.279
-eating with a spork.
-Hang on.

02:35.947 --> 02:37.323
Yeah?

02:37.406 --> 02:38.783
703 (over phone):
Hey, it's 703.

02:38.825 --> 02:40.952
-Go, 703.
-How's your day going?

02:40.994 --> 02:42.704
Oh, life's a cabaret.

02:42.787 --> 02:45.623
-Go.
-Packers/Rams over 52.

02:45.707 --> 02:47.208
Titans plus six.

02:47.292 --> 02:48.918
Dime on each. It's all I got.

02:48.960 --> 02:50.170
-Thanks.
-All right,

02:50.253 --> 02:52.881
you're down. Good luck, 703.

02:52.964 --> 02:54.591
(phone beeps)

02:54.632 --> 02:56.760
All right, I'm sorry.
I'll come by later.

02:56.801 --> 02:58.595
SANDRA:
You know, if you let me
open up a checking account,

02:58.636 --> 03:00.263
I wouldn't have to bother you
like this.

03:00.305 --> 03:01.848
Honey, what are the
two conditions I gave you

03:01.931 --> 03:03.224
before we got married?

03:03.308 --> 03:05.852
-No banks, no musicals.
-I love you.

03:05.935 --> 03:07.437
Goodbye.

03:08.313 --> 03:11.441
♪ What a fool believes... ♪

03:11.483 --> 03:13.485
DANNY:
All right, how'd we do?

03:13.526 --> 03:15.820
I didn't count it.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.405
He's usually good.

03:17.489 --> 03:19.032
♪ The power... ♪

03:19.115 --> 03:20.825
Do we have to listen to this?

03:20.867 --> 03:23.703
I like it, all right?
Leave it alone.

03:24.913 --> 03:28.083
♪ What seems... ♪

03:28.166 --> 03:29.834
-The fuck?
-What?

03:29.876 --> 03:32.087
Money, it reeks.

03:32.170 --> 03:34.339
(sniffs, grunts)

03:34.381 --> 03:37.425
-Tell me that's not shit.
-That is shit.

03:39.344 --> 03:40.929
Son of a bitch
wiped his ass with it.

03:41.012 --> 03:43.348
Or maybe he used it
to scoop up dog poo.

03:43.390 --> 03:46.309
It's not dog poop.
This is human poop.

03:46.351 --> 03:47.852
Oh, like you know
the difference.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.688
Do dogs eat onions?

03:49.771 --> 03:51.356
Use your head.

03:51.439 --> 03:53.358
-(engine starts)
-That motherfucker.

03:53.400 --> 03:55.902
Nothing pisses me off
more than people.

03:57.529 --> 03:59.948
♪ To be ♪

04:00.031 --> 04:03.535
♪ Is always better
than nothing ♪

04:05.078 --> 04:08.832
♪ Than nothing at all. ♪

04:10.834 --> 04:13.044
DANNY:
Roger that, 238. 100 bucks,

04:13.128 --> 04:14.587
Winnipeg on the puck line,

04:14.671 --> 04:16.380
and you want under
on the grand salami.

04:17.007 --> 04:18.632
Smart. Good luck.

04:18.716 --> 04:20.093
("A Horse with No Name"
by America playing over radio)

04:20.176 --> 04:21.636
You got that?

04:21.720 --> 04:24.139
Yeah, but, man,
do we have to listen to this?

04:24.222 --> 04:27.225
Would you stop complaining
and take in the message?

04:27.267 --> 04:28.727
(sighs)

04:28.768 --> 04:30.437
Okay.

04:30.520 --> 04:32.939
Stewie Malenkovich. Eight large.

04:33.023 --> 04:34.566
That's a lot of green
for a waiter.

04:34.649 --> 04:36.234
He's a maître d',
and, yeah, it is.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.695
-Want me to take this?
-No, I got to go talk to him,

04:38.737 --> 04:41.322
bring his number down.
Just hang out.

04:41.406 --> 04:44.784
♪ You can't remember your name
'cause there ain't no one ♪

04:44.868 --> 04:46.870
♪ For to give you no pain ♪

04:46.911 --> 04:49.581
-(singing along)
-♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪

04:49.622 --> 04:51.374
♪ La, la, la... ♪

04:51.416 --> 04:53.835
-Oh, hell no.
-(music stops)

04:53.918 --> 04:55.712
-♪ Just give me the paper... ♪
-Yeah, all right.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.006
(song continues indistinctly)

05:00.592 --> 05:02.886
-How you doing?
-We're not open yet.

05:02.927 --> 05:06.181
Yeah, I know. I'm looking
for a, uh, Stewie Malenkovich.

05:06.264 --> 05:07.515
He no longer works here.

05:07.599 --> 05:10.602
Shit. You know where
I could find him?

05:10.685 --> 05:12.562
Sorry.

05:18.026 --> 05:19.110
Stewie?

05:20.195 --> 05:21.321
Is that you?

05:22.197 --> 05:25.075
Oh, my God, it is you.

05:25.116 --> 05:26.451
What the hell's going on?

05:26.534 --> 05:28.787
Please, not here.

05:28.870 --> 05:31.456
Is this like a Halloween thing?

05:31.539 --> 05:33.667
Are you trying
to hurt my feelings?

05:33.750 --> 05:35.210
No, no, I'm just confused.

05:35.293 --> 05:38.129
If you must know,
after many heartbreaking years,

05:38.171 --> 05:41.925
-I've decided to live my truth.
-Your truth?

05:41.966 --> 05:44.135
So, question, does your truth
include paying the money

05:44.177 --> 05:45.720
you lost betting on the WNBA?

05:45.804 --> 05:48.848
Nobody bets on the girls.
(sighs) I thought I had an edge.

05:48.932 --> 05:50.933
-Where's my money?
-I...

05:50.975 --> 05:52.977
I don't have it.

05:53.019 --> 05:54.813
Jesus...

05:54.854 --> 05:55.939
(both grunt)

05:55.980 --> 05:57.482
-The fuck?
-I know this is where

05:57.565 --> 05:59.150
you guys break legs and noses,

05:59.192 --> 06:01.653
but I spent a lot of money
to look pretty,

06:01.736 --> 06:04.322
and I'm not gonna
let you mess it up!

06:04.364 --> 06:05.824
(grunts) I wasn't gonna hit you.

06:05.907 --> 06:06.950
Liar!

06:06.991 --> 06:08.702
♪ Goodness gracious, the paper ♪

06:08.785 --> 06:09.911
-♪ Where the cash at? ♪
-(grunting)

06:09.994 --> 06:12.038
♪ Where the stash at... ♪

06:12.122 --> 06:13.998
How'd it go? Oh.

06:14.040 --> 06:15.500
Urgent care. You drive.

06:15.583 --> 06:16.835
What happened?

06:16.918 --> 06:19.337
I don't want to talk about it.

06:19.379 --> 06:21.673
♪ One in the chamber,
32 in the clip ♪

06:21.715 --> 06:22.841
♪ Motherfuckers better strip ♪

06:22.924 --> 06:24.384
♪ Yeah, nigga, peel ♪

06:24.467 --> 06:26.011
♪ Before you find out how... ♪

06:26.052 --> 06:27.804
Shit makes me nervous.

06:27.846 --> 06:31.057
♪ You talk a good game. ♪

06:33.727 --> 06:37.147
You know, I can pop that
back in for you real quick.

06:37.188 --> 06:39.024
-No, thanks.
-You sure?

06:39.107 --> 06:41.026
When I was in the league, man,
dislocated finger

06:41.067 --> 06:42.694
was just a part
of doing business.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.863
I-I-I prefer
a medical professional.

06:44.946 --> 06:46.448
We used to straighten them out
for each other

06:46.531 --> 06:47.824
right in the huddle.

06:47.866 --> 06:49.117
Pass.

06:49.200 --> 06:50.493
Suit yourself.

06:50.534 --> 06:53.079
Probably need X-rays anyway.

06:53.163 --> 06:55.206
She kicked me in the ribs
pretty good.

06:55.290 --> 06:57.375
-She?
-Yeah.

06:57.417 --> 06:58.418
Stewie's a girl now.

06:58.501 --> 07:00.587
No shit.

07:01.796 --> 07:03.465
Does Stewie identify as a girl?

07:03.548 --> 07:06.176
-How the fuck should I know?
-It's important these days.

07:06.217 --> 07:08.219
People are sensitive
about their pronouns.

07:08.261 --> 07:10.055
You punch me in the face, I get
to call you any pronoun I want.

07:10.138 --> 07:11.639
I'm just trying
to point something out.

07:11.723 --> 07:14.476
-Point this.
-Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

07:14.559 --> 07:16.644
You should be.

07:19.439 --> 07:22.609
-(bones crack)
-(screams) The f...

07:22.692 --> 07:24.903
-(screams) Fuck!
-We're good.

07:24.944 --> 07:26.905
We're good.

07:27.822 --> 07:29.574
SANDRA:
This is disgusting.

07:29.657 --> 07:31.576
DANNY:
Well, what do you want from me?
It's money.

07:31.659 --> 07:33.328
Smells like it was
up somebody's ass.

07:33.411 --> 07:35.038
Oh, people don't trust banks.

07:35.080 --> 07:37.207
They keep their money
where they think it's safe.

07:37.248 --> 07:38.832
Oh, don't even. Ugh.

07:38.917 --> 07:40.418
What, you don't want it?
Give it back.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.753
I didn't say that.

07:41.795 --> 07:43.505
You know what else
you didn't say?

07:43.588 --> 07:46.257
"Oh, honey, who punched you in
the face and broke your finger?"

07:46.299 --> 07:47.884
You told me not to ask
about your business.

07:47.926 --> 07:49.594
You could express
some compassion.

07:49.678 --> 07:51.388
I said "yikes"
when you walked in.

07:51.429 --> 07:52.764
-Never mind.
-(sighs)

07:52.806 --> 07:54.099
Jesus, how did this
become my life?

07:54.140 --> 07:57.102
Oh, really?
You want to go there?

07:57.185 --> 08:00.647
You want to examine your life
pre-Danny Colavito?

08:00.730 --> 08:02.774
-Don't start with the...
-Yeah, the single mother

08:02.857 --> 08:06.486
slinging cocktails at Binion's
motherfucking Horseshoe,

08:06.569 --> 08:08.321
-graveyard shift.
-I was doing just fine.

08:08.405 --> 08:09.447
I had my dignity.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.448
-Oh, did you?
-Yeah.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.783
Because I remember on our

08:11.866 --> 08:13.284
second date,
you bursting into tears,

08:13.326 --> 08:15.286
begging me to take you away
from all this.

08:15.328 --> 08:17.080
I was crying because I realized
you were the best I could do.

08:17.122 --> 08:18.873
DANNY:
And you were probably right.

08:18.957 --> 08:21.626
What other idiot's gonna
buy you a three-bedroom house

08:21.710 --> 08:23.962
and set you up in some
bullshit boutique

08:24.045 --> 08:26.798
selling God knows what the fuck
on Ventura Boulevard?

08:26.881 --> 08:28.967
SANDRA:
It's an upscale gift shop
with offbeat gifts.

08:29.050 --> 08:30.593
DANNY:
It's a money pit that
I wash money through.

08:30.635 --> 08:32.554
-SANDRA: Oh, yeah? Yeah?
-DANNY: Yeah.

08:32.636 --> 08:34.972
SANDRA:
Then why does Selena Gomez
only buy her candles from me?

08:35.056 --> 08:37.726
DANNY:
Oh, I take it back. You sold
a candle to a crazy broad.

08:37.808 --> 08:40.020
So, Anthony, what are you?

08:40.102 --> 08:42.813
Some kind of a pirate
or something?

08:42.897 --> 08:45.316
I'm Lavi From D.Gray-man.

08:45.358 --> 08:46.860
Lavi.

08:46.943 --> 08:49.154
Is D.Gray-man a TV show?

08:49.195 --> 08:52.824
(sighs) It's a manga
that also became an anime.

08:52.907 --> 08:54.617
-Oh.
-DANNY: I love you!

08:54.659 --> 08:57.162
I have no idea
what you just said.

08:58.747 --> 09:00.165
Come on, we got to go.

09:00.206 --> 09:02.834
-All right, kid, see you later.
-Bye, Ray.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.171
See you later, Lavi.
Here's a 20.

09:06.212 --> 09:09.049
-Go have some fun.
-Thanks, Danny.

09:10.675 --> 09:12.802
Looking good.

09:18.183 --> 09:20.185
(sniffs)
Ugh.

09:31.279 --> 09:33.740
(doorbell buzzes)

09:33.823 --> 09:35.700
-DANNY (over monitor): Hi.
-Hey.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.494
You want to buzz us in,
Lorraine?

09:37.535 --> 09:39.537
What's the secret password?

09:39.579 --> 09:41.206
Not now, Lorraine.

09:41.289 --> 09:42.957
(door buzzes)

09:42.999 --> 09:45.710
All right.

09:49.297 --> 09:51.007
-Hey.
-Hey.

09:51.049 --> 09:53.051
Jesus, what happened to you?

09:53.093 --> 09:56.346
Your brother learned about
gender sensitivity. (grunts)

09:57.305 --> 09:59.641
Here's the calls for today.
How's the online action?

09:59.724 --> 10:01.726
Busy. Thursday night's game
is all K.C.

10:01.810 --> 10:03.770
All right, move the line a half
and, uh...

10:03.853 --> 10:04.896
we're writing off
the Malenkovich debt.

10:04.979 --> 10:06.898
What? That's a big number, D.

10:06.940 --> 10:09.651
-Just write it off.
-Well, did you at least
let Ray wind him up?

10:09.734 --> 10:11.069
I'm mostly a visual deterrent.

10:11.152 --> 10:13.405
Listen, the days
of breaking legs are over, okay?

10:13.446 --> 10:16.533
-I'm not gonna do anything that
puts the cops on my ass.
-You're such a puss.

10:16.574 --> 10:17.867
A puss that doesn't need

10:17.909 --> 10:19.244
to join the Aryan Nation
to take a shower.

10:19.327 --> 10:21.579
Listen, let me just
make a phone call.

10:21.621 --> 10:23.039
No, that's not how
I do business.

10:23.081 --> 10:24.582
What kind of business allows
a guy to walk

10:24.624 --> 10:25.959
-on six grand?
-DANNY: Eight grand.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.836
Every business.
It's called shrinkage.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.797
Listen, all retail operators
factor in

10:30.880 --> 10:31.923
losses due to shoplifting,

10:32.007 --> 10:34.050
bad checks, what have you.

10:34.092 --> 10:35.427
It's called shrinkage,
look it up.

10:35.468 --> 10:36.469
I'll tell you what's shrinking.

10:36.553 --> 10:37.846
Don't.

10:37.929 --> 10:39.139
We're all thinking it,
that's enough.

10:39.222 --> 10:41.641
Fuck you both.
Just write it off.

10:41.725 --> 10:44.060
Fine. Oh, I do have
some good news.

10:44.102 --> 10:44.853
Tell me.

10:44.936 --> 10:45.979
I found Charlie Sheen.

10:46.062 --> 10:47.522
-DANNY: Really?
-Yes.

10:47.605 --> 10:49.441
-Where is that fuckwad?
-LORRAINE: In Malibu.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.443
A rehab called
Freedom from Bondage House.

10:51.526 --> 10:54.404
-How'd you find him?
-TMZ. Paparazzi
got a picture of him

10:54.446 --> 10:56.740
-walking in the back door.
-Let's roll.

10:56.781 --> 10:58.283
Just got to make a quick stop.

10:58.324 --> 10:59.743
I'm not waiting in the car
while you get laid.

10:59.784 --> 11:01.786
You're welcome.

11:09.461 --> 11:12.714
Yo, it's me. I got two pounds
ready to go.

11:12.797 --> 11:14.341
No, I'm not selling
on consignment.

11:14.424 --> 11:16.134
You pay for it up front,
or grow your own shrooms.

11:16.217 --> 11:19.512
Train Town, Griffith Park,
one hour, bring cash.

11:19.596 --> 11:21.139
No, you can't Venmo me.

11:21.222 --> 11:23.600
I'm not cutting
your fucking hair.

11:23.641 --> 11:26.644
♪ Talk to me some more ♪

11:26.728 --> 11:29.606
♪ You don't have to go ♪

11:29.647 --> 11:32.984
♪ You're the poetry man ♪

11:33.026 --> 11:36.696
♪ You make things all rhyme,
yeah, yeah... ♪

11:36.780 --> 11:38.490
(sighs)

11:39.866 --> 11:41.201
(engine turns off)

11:41.284 --> 11:42.994
(sighs) You know,
I hope she appreciates

11:43.078 --> 11:45.330
-what a wonderful
grandson you are.
-She doesn't.

11:46.456 --> 11:48.165
Yo, what you need that for?

11:48.249 --> 11:50.335
No offense, but are we
or are we not in the hood?

11:50.418 --> 11:51.795
Excuse me?

11:51.836 --> 11:54.172
But "hood" is short
for "neighborhood,"

11:54.214 --> 11:56.091
with an emphasis on "neighbor."

11:56.174 --> 11:59.177
What do you want from me, Ray?
I'm scared.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.970
(sighs)

12:10.814 --> 12:12.732
LAMAR:
Yo, NFL.

12:12.816 --> 12:14.693
You got old, man.

12:14.776 --> 12:16.403
You keep talking, and you won't.

12:16.486 --> 12:17.987
Look here,

12:18.029 --> 12:20.198
20 bucks, watch the truck.

12:21.658 --> 12:23.034
-(grunts)
-(laughs)

12:23.076 --> 12:25.161
See, Danny,
these are good kids, man.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.460
Yeah.

12:32.544 --> 12:34.212
They're the future.

12:34.254 --> 12:35.296
(sighs)

12:35.380 --> 12:38.717
Uh-huh. (laughs)
What you think, Grandma?

12:38.758 --> 12:40.677
50 inches,

12:40.719 --> 12:42.637
beautiful picture.

12:42.721 --> 12:44.514
Is it hot?

12:44.556 --> 12:46.224
No.

12:46.307 --> 12:49.477
I don't care about no TV.
I want my house back.

12:49.519 --> 12:50.854
Can we please not do this now?

12:50.895 --> 12:54.315
See this? I used to live here.

12:54.399 --> 12:56.609
It's in a cul-de-sac
in Brentwood.

12:56.693 --> 12:57.902
That's a nice part of town.

12:57.944 --> 12:59.904
I lived next door
to Judd Apatow.

12:59.988 --> 13:02.240
Now look at me.

13:02.323 --> 13:06.077
I live next door
to an oil derrick.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.246
I'm doing the best I can.

13:08.329 --> 13:09.873
I want to go back to Brentwood.

13:09.914 --> 13:11.624
