18:26.773 --> 18:29.067
Oh, I'm sorry,
but guests are not allowed.

18:29.150 --> 18:32.153
Well, what about family?
I'm his cousin,

18:32.237 --> 18:33.446
Danny Sheen.

18:33.530 --> 18:35.740
Family is allowed on Family Day,

18:35.824 --> 18:37.742
which is the third Sunday
of every month.

18:37.826 --> 18:41.121
That's not gonna work.
Where is he?

18:41.204 --> 18:43.415
I'm sorry,
but I can't let you in.

18:43.456 --> 18:45.959
Fuck it, let's go find him.

18:46.042 --> 18:48.461
Security. Reception.

18:51.256 --> 18:55.010
Sorry, fellas,
you can't come in.

18:55.093 --> 18:57.554
I can't do this again. Ray?

18:58.471 --> 19:00.557
-How much do you make an hour?
-What?

19:00.598 --> 19:02.976
How much do you make? Ten, 12?

19:03.059 --> 19:04.102
Fifteen.

19:04.144 --> 19:06.062
Not bad.

19:06.104 --> 19:08.398
You get medical insurance?

19:09.816 --> 19:11.526
Have a nice day.

19:14.112 --> 19:16.322
Hi, I'm Ashley.
I'm an alcoholic,

19:16.406 --> 19:17.949
a drug addict, a sex addict,

19:18.033 --> 19:20.160
and I have an eating disorder.

19:20.243 --> 19:21.745
GROUP:
Hi, Ashley.

19:21.786 --> 19:24.122
Excuse me, guys, um, has anybody
here seen Charlie Sheen?

19:24.164 --> 19:26.082
-Who?
-No? No Charlie?

19:26.124 --> 19:27.792
As you were.

19:32.213 --> 19:35.383
Just gonna...
take a mini muffin.

19:37.969 --> 19:39.846
You see what's-her-name
back there, the porn star?

19:39.929 --> 19:41.389
I did.

19:41.473 --> 19:43.641
Ever notice there's
no porn supporting actors?

19:43.683 --> 19:46.644
-They're all stars.
-Everybody's a quarterback.

19:46.686 --> 19:48.730
(birds chirping)

19:50.106 --> 19:52.317
(crying)

19:56.488 --> 19:59.491
Excuse me.
You seen Charlie Sheen?

19:59.532 --> 20:00.617
Who?

20:01.701 --> 20:03.787
He was in Two and a Half Men.

20:04.788 --> 20:06.164
Sitcom.

20:06.247 --> 20:08.166
Never mind.

20:08.208 --> 20:10.919
Hold on, hold on.
Have some compassion.

20:12.587 --> 20:14.464
That's a beautiful view.

20:16.174 --> 20:17.926
What is that, Catalina?

20:18.009 --> 20:21.721
-That's got to help.
-(continues crying)

20:24.224 --> 20:26.685
Okay, think good thoughts.

20:27.852 --> 20:30.146
Eugene, it's on you.

20:30.188 --> 20:31.940
Fifty.

20:32.023 --> 20:33.525
(sighs)

20:33.608 --> 20:34.484
Call.

20:34.526 --> 20:37.487
-Angus?
-And... 50.

20:37.529 --> 20:38.697
Oh, someone's feeling lucky.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.198
I don't need luck to beat you.

20:40.240 --> 20:41.950
(laughter)

20:42.033 --> 20:43.493
What happened to this kid?

20:43.535 --> 20:45.036
He used to be so cute.

20:45.078 --> 20:46.371
He gruesome.

20:46.413 --> 20:48.206
(laughter)

20:48.289 --> 20:50.709
Hey, there's my guy.

20:50.792 --> 20:53.753
Oh, shit. Danny.

20:53.837 --> 20:55.380
Ray.

20:55.463 --> 20:56.589
Jesus, what happened to you?

20:56.673 --> 20:59.217
Little scuffle. No big deal.

20:59.300 --> 21:01.094
You should see the other girl.

21:01.970 --> 21:04.723
So, what-what-what-what
brings you here?

21:04.806 --> 21:08.101
What kind of question is that?
We were concerned about you.

21:08.184 --> 21:10.854
Oh, you thought that...
(laughs) No, no, no, no, I am,

21:10.895 --> 21:13.857
I'm clean as a whistle.
I just run a game here.

21:15.066 --> 21:16.526
In a rehab?

21:16.568 --> 21:19.529
Yeah. There's no guns,
the food is terrific,

21:19.571 --> 21:22.532
and there's ample parking.

21:23.908 --> 21:25.368
Could we talk to you
for a minute?

21:25.410 --> 21:27.412
Of course.

21:27.495 --> 21:29.414
Deal me out.

21:34.044 --> 21:35.712
How'd you find this place?

21:35.754 --> 21:37.589
Oh, I've gotten sober here
many times.

21:37.672 --> 21:39.883
It's a wonderful program.
The owner's a buddy.

21:39.924 --> 21:42.302
-He lets me rent the room.
-Nice.

21:42.385 --> 21:43.762
So, what's it cost
to get the cure here?

21:43.803 --> 21:46.097
Last time I got a nudge
from the judge?

21:46.139 --> 21:47.932
-About 75 grand a month.
-(scoffs)

21:48.016 --> 21:49.517
I'm in the wrong business.

21:49.601 --> 21:52.228
You know, that's not too far off
how much you owe us.

21:52.270 --> 21:55.357
Really?
'Cause I-I-I had it lower.

21:55.440 --> 21:57.275
You had it wrong.

21:57.317 --> 21:58.610
(scoffs) Come on.

21:58.693 --> 22:00.862
You know me,
I'm always good for it.

22:00.945 --> 22:02.238
Are you?

22:02.280 --> 22:03.615
'Cause I seem to recall

22:03.656 --> 22:05.617
having to push
your Maybach off a cliff.

22:05.658 --> 22:07.118
You didn't push shit.

22:07.160 --> 22:08.578
Ray pushed it.

22:08.620 --> 22:10.288
It was an S-Class.

22:10.372 --> 22:11.623
Who cares? I swear,

22:11.706 --> 22:12.999
you will get your money.

22:13.083 --> 22:15.502
I am, I am this close
to being a judge

22:15.585 --> 22:16.961
on Japan's Got Talent.

22:17.045 --> 22:19.172
Oh, terrific.
What kind of watch is that?

22:19.255 --> 22:21.174
This? Oh, this-this is...

22:21.257 --> 22:22.967
a cheap knockoff.
Garbage.

22:23.009 --> 22:25.303
-Let me see it.
-(scoffs) Danny, come on.

22:25.345 --> 22:26.680
-It's-it's junk.
-Ray?

22:26.763 --> 22:28.431
All right, whoa, whoa, whoa.

22:28.473 --> 22:30.433
Slow down. Take it easy.

22:30.475 --> 22:33.561
Look at me, visually deterring.

22:35.855 --> 22:36.690
Richard "Milly"?

22:36.773 --> 22:38.817
Ah, it's actually Richard Mille.

22:38.900 --> 22:41.653
Richard Mille.

22:41.736 --> 22:43.988
That's a douche way to say it.

22:44.072 --> 22:45.365
Google this, please.

22:45.448 --> 22:46.825
Wi-Fi password?

22:46.866 --> 22:49.077
-"Serenity."
-Of course it is.

22:49.160 --> 22:52.622
It's, uh, M-I-L-L-E.

22:54.666 --> 22:57.085
You talk to that Jon Cryer much?

22:57.168 --> 22:58.962
Not for a long time, no.

22:59.004 --> 23:00.547
He was a hoot.

23:02.173 --> 23:03.466
He's my favorite.

23:03.508 --> 23:06.177
It was really more
an ensemble show.

23:06.219 --> 23:07.846
RAY:
Son of a bitch.

23:07.929 --> 23:08.805
What?

23:08.847 --> 23:12.017
That thing is 150 grand, used.

23:12.058 --> 23:14.686
Charlie, I thought
we were friends.

23:14.769 --> 23:17.230
We are friends,
but I only owe you 75.

23:17.313 --> 23:20.025
-Charlie, Charlie, Charlie...
-Okay, okay, hold on, hold on.

23:20.066 --> 23:23.028
What if I make this right
with some baseball memorabilia?

23:23.069 --> 23:24.863
Guys, guys,

23:24.946 --> 23:28.575
I've got Babe Ruth's
autopsy report.

23:28.658 --> 23:30.410
-Stop.
-Okay.

23:30.493 --> 23:32.579
Okay, uh, uh, how about the hat

23:32.662 --> 23:35.540
Barry Bonds wore when he had
a regular-sized head?

23:37.083 --> 23:38.209
Are you done?

23:38.293 --> 23:40.211
Yeah.

23:40.253 --> 23:42.213
Listen.

23:42.297 --> 23:44.341
I like you.

23:44.382 --> 23:45.800
I really do.

23:45.884 --> 23:48.178
And I admire how you turned
your life around.

23:48.219 --> 23:50.847
Well, thank you, thank you.
I have been working very hard,

23:50.889 --> 23:52.557
you know.
I-It's all about the journey.

23:52.599 --> 23:55.060
Whoa, whoa, whoa, enough.

23:56.728 --> 23:58.229
I'm gonna tell you something

23:58.313 --> 24:00.523
I never told a client ever.

24:01.399 --> 24:02.734
I'm listening.

24:02.776 --> 24:05.236
You shouldn't bet on sports.

24:05.320 --> 24:07.155
You shouldn't bet on anything.

24:07.238 --> 24:11.409
I mean, if someone's
giving you odds that Wednesday

24:11.451 --> 24:14.746
follows Tuesday, you say,
"Nah, I'm good."

24:14.788 --> 24:18.708
But, Danny, it's all I got left.

24:18.750 --> 24:22.587
I understand, but nevertheless,
for a guy like you,

24:22.671 --> 24:24.923
no bueno.

24:24.964 --> 24:27.425
Okay. I hear you.

24:27.509 --> 24:29.719
I appreciate
your concern, and...

24:29.761 --> 24:31.054
I'm gonna take it to heart.

24:31.096 --> 24:33.098
Good.

24:33.139 --> 24:34.933
Let's go.

24:42.607 --> 24:44.734
Hey. What was that all about?

24:44.776 --> 24:46.945
I need a new bookie.

24:50.156 --> 24:52.951
(laughter)

24:54.661 --> 24:55.954
What am I missing?

24:56.037 --> 24:58.790
Thing tells time,
whoop-dee-fucking-doo.

24:58.832 --> 25:00.500
If you don't like it,
let me wear it.

25:00.583 --> 25:01.751
No.

25:01.793 --> 25:03.628
(laughs) Hey, buddy.

25:03.712 --> 25:05.755
We need another pitcher
of the margaritas.

25:05.797 --> 25:07.215
With Don Julio?

25:07.298 --> 25:09.259
We'll take the cheap shit
on the second pass.

25:09.300 --> 25:10.677
-(laughter)
-You got it.

25:12.095 --> 25:13.471
DANNY:
So,

25:13.513 --> 25:14.764
here's what I don't understand.

25:14.806 --> 25:16.433
Pot's off the table,

25:16.474 --> 25:20.061
